parameters: Clea: May I ask you about the priestess Sophia?
Farmer Gala: She used to be a regular here.

Thief Nora: A regular at the farm... Are you a vegetable
thief!?

Farmer Gala: Haha, no way! There used to be a tavern here
until a year ago.

Farmer Gala: It used to be my father's shop, but it burned
down in a fire. It may sound strange coming from me, but it
was a great place where regulars would gather.

Farmer Gala: Haha, go tell those noble folks at the campus!
Taking away the entertainment from us farmers is their idea
of fun.

Farmer Gala: I pleaded many times, but before I could see
the reopened shop, my father passed away.
Clea: Thank you for telling me even the difficult things.

Farmer Gala: It's just a complaint, but Sophia might be in
the town of Campus.

Farmer Gala: There's a tavern in that town, so keep it a
secret that you heard it from me, okay?
Farmer Gala: Ah, the smell of wine brings back memories...
Farmer Gara: Sorry, but I'm counting on you for the wood.

Clea: The procurement of the requested lumber is complete.
The members of the Bulk Brigade will deliver it soon.

Sophia the Priestess: It seems that members of the Bulk
Brigade will stay behind. With this, I believe mercenaries
won't be able to act recklessly.
Farmer Gala: That will be helpful. Thank you so much!
Clea: What should we do next?

Farmer Gala: Now we just need to secure the bard and the
alcohol... Once the building is complete, I'll contact the
guild!

Farmer Gala: If I take care of securing the alcohol, I think
we should have someone go and find the bard.
Clea: I'm looking forward to the tavern being built.

Farmer Gala: Ah, I'm really looking forward to it! We'll
reclaim this place as a haven from the nobles!

Farmer Gala: Please take this! I think it's quite valuable
in its own way.
Farmer Gala: I can't wait for the wood to arrive.
Pursuer Opis: ...Please stop getting involved with me.

Mage Relm: I heard about searching for books, but what kind
of books are they? I'm a collector, so please ask me
anything!
Tracker Opis: ...Just ordinary cookbooks, nothing special.

Mage Relm: Sigh... I thought they would be special
grimoires...
Clea: Is there any kind of clue?
Tracker Opis: The location is at the inn in Campos.

Mage Relm: If you know that much, why don't you go meet them
yourself!?

Tracker Opis: I can't go into details, but there's a reason
behind it. The books were taken by a man named Terra without
permission.

Tracker Opis: Well... Terra doesn't realize their true
value, though.
Clea: Should I come back here after obtaining them?

Tracker Opis: I want you to deliver them to the Bandit's
Prairie. Well then.
Clea: Seems like there's a complicated situation.

Mage Relm: Cookbooks might be a lie, so just to be safe, let
me handle the book retrieval!
Clea: Understood, please leave it to me.

Farmer Woman: I can't say it out loud with a loud voice, but
that war with Tarasa was not something that should have been
done. Campus has changed because of that war.

Farmer Woman: I can't say it out loud with a loud voice, but
that war with Tarasa changed Campus. That war shouldn't have
happened.

Farmer's Wife: Are you a traveler? It's a place with nothing

Farmer's Wife: You shouldn't trouble Eleo-chan too much,
okay?

Sister Eleo: Thank you very much for this opportunity. I
will take responsibility for the rehabilitation!

Clea: Understood, I will relay that to the Adventurer's

Sister Eleo: Alright, from today onwards, I will train you

Sister Sophia: Hey, do you mind if I make a request?
Clea: It depends on the content.

Sister Sophia: I don't think I can do it alone, so when

Disheartened Woman: Hic... Ahaha, I'm fine, don't worry.

Sister Eleo: I smell alcohol! I thought you were seriously
injured!

Disheartened Woman: Ahaha, I might have a serious injury,

Sister Eleo: Injured people don't get this drunk! Seriously,
come inside and rest.

Disheartened Woman: There are injuries that you can't see,
young lady.

Sister Eleo: Healing is also our job. Using alcohol to heal
is just a temporary mood booster, it doesn't heal the heart.

Disheartened Woman: Impressive words... I wonder if even
someone like me can aspire to be a doctor.

Sister Eleo: Yes, of course! I will take care of you

Sister Eleo: I am Eleo. And you?
Sophia: I... um, my name is Sophia. I am a little doctor.

Sister Eleo: Being little is unnecessary! Hehe, please come

Priestess Sophia: I apologize for the wait.
Clea: Were you able to say goodbye?

Priestess Sophia: Once again, I am Priestess Sophia. I will

Priestess Sophia: I will chase after the dragons with all of

parameters:
Mage Relm: Could it be that she drank too much and fell into
the river!?

Thief Nora: She didn't drink at all today! She had a rare
expression, looking absent-minded.

Thief Nora: ...I can hear Sophia-san's voice. It seems like
she's with Eleo-san.
Sister Eleo: Sophia-san, are you okay?

Priestess Sophia: Yes, I'm fine. It's good that I was
finally able to repay the villagers' kindness.

Priestess Sophia: You know... I've never really been thanked
or shown gratitude like this before.

Priestess Sophia: That's why I feel strange, being thanked
by everyone... I don't know what to do.
Sister Eleo: It's simple, just smile back with a smile.

Sister Eleo: And besides, I've always been grateful. It's
just that Sophia-san didn't realize it.

Sister Eleo: Not just me, but Clea-san and everyone in Irini
Village feels the same way.

Sister Eleo: So, I'll say it again, Sophia-san... Thank you
always.

Priestess Sophia: Let me say it too, Eleo-chan... Thank you
so much for everything you always do.

Sister Eleo: That's right, please tell us about your
journey, Sophia-san. Your stories are popular at the
orphanage, you know.
Priestess Sophia: Hehe, I wonder what I should talk about.
Clea: Let's have some time just the two of us today.
Sister Eleo: Is something the matter, everyone?
Clea: I have a favor to ask today.

Sister Eleo: ...The problem of resolving the request from
the Imiserinos Shrine Maiden is to prevent humans from
turning into ogres.

Sister Sophia: You don't have to push yourself too hard,
okay? It's a request that we received.
Sister Eleo: Why didn't you rely on us from the beginning?

Sister Sophia: I didn't want to make Sister Eleo go through
a scary experience like with the dragon.

Sister Eleo: For Sister Sophia, I may be just a child, but I
have a duty as a Terios Church priestess.

Sister Eleo: You came here thinking of me as your mentor,
right?

Sister Sophia: At first, when I thought of Eleo-chan, I
imagined her angry face, her serious face, and her smiling
face.

Sister Sophia: There might be scary things happening at our
destination.

Sister Sophia: But I want you to come with me as my mentor
to save Goats-san.

Sister Eleo: Of course! As a priestess, as a mentor, and as
a friend, I will go with you!

Clea: Thank you. Let's go to the Bulk Corps' garrison where
Goats-san is.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Priestess Sophia: Eleo-chan, I have come here on behalf of
Goat-san's request. I would like to ask for your cooperation
in resolving this.

Sister Eleo: Leave it to me! I have also prepared myself to
help with the resolution.

Sister Eleo: I will definitely rescue Goat-san and the
others.
Clea: It's reassuring. Please take care of us.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Sister Eleo: You have a stern expression, is something the
matter?
Priestess Sophia: Clea-chan, may I speak?
Clea: Yes, I think that would be better.

Sister Eleo: Caron-sama is like that... and there might even
be a dragon...!

Priestess Sophia: I know it may be hard to believe, but
everything I've said is true.

Priestess Sophia: Once we are prepared, we will head to the
royal palace to reclaim the throne.
Sister Eleo: Did you come here today to say goodbye?

Priestess Sophia: Hehe, I met Sister Eleo in this place.
It's truly a coincidence that I was able to meet you.

Priestess Sophia: At first, I thought you were a cheeky
child, but seeing you confidently carry out your duties as a
priestess was dazzling.
Priestess Sophia: ...Above all, I was truly envious.

Sister Eleo: Please let me participate in reclaiming the
throne as well.

Sister Eleo: I understand that you didn't come here with
that intention.

Sister Eleo: In the previous battle with the dragon, I
participated strictly as a [collaborator].

Sister Eleo: But this time, I want to fight against the
monsters as a guide of Priestess Sophia and as a duty of the
Terios Church's priest.
Priestess Sophia: I'm really happy that you say that.

Priestess Sophia: But before making the final decision,
there is something I must confess to you.

Former Shadow Alicia: My real name is Alicia. I used to be a
former interrogator belonging to the Alicia Empire's shadow
division, Ishekel.

Former Shadow Alicia: My job was something completely
different from being a priestess. Breaking and healing,
breaking and healing, I did that every single day.

Former Shadow Alicia: That's why I might have admired being
a priestess. Because I can use the same [healing power] for
the right reasons.

Former Shadow Alicia: Even after hearing this confession,
will Sister Eleo still fight alongside us?

Former Shadow Alicia: Will you still be my guiding light,
even with my sinful past?
Sister Eleo: I cannot forgive you.

Sister Eleo: It's not something that can be resolved just by
me forgiving you. You said you were a former interrogator,
but your actions are not in the past.

Sister Eleo: That's why people must live righteously, so
they don't commit sins that will never disappear.
Former Shadow Alicia: Then, can I not become a priestess?

Sister Eleo: That's not true. It is the ability of humans to
change something.

Sister Eleo: And you have changed many things and saved many
people as a priestess.

Sister Eleo: I am also one of the people who was saved by
you.

Sister Eleo: I acknowledge your sins, but still, I want to
be your guiding light.

Sister Eleo: Now, please take my hand. It is your mission to
save many people with this hand.
Sister Eleo: Let's walk together, Priestess Sophia.
Priestess Sophia: Thank you... Sister Eleo.
Priestess Sophia: I'm really glad I met you...
